<FIRST>r w PM-Durenberger-EthicsLetter     04-30 0233</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Durenberger-Ethics Letter,230</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-Durenberger</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Here is the text of the letter from the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Select </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> on Ethics to Sen. <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON>, R-Minn., on its investigation of his public comments on intelligence matters: Dear Senator <PERSON> Durenberger </PERSON>: The Select Committee has received and investigated allegations that certain of your public statements violated <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> Resolution 400 <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> Resolution 400 prohibits the disclosure of classified intelligence information which has been provided to the <ORGANIZATION> Select </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> on </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Intelligence </ORGANIZATION>, and imposes a duty upon each senator to exercise special care when discussing intelligence matters. As the immediate former chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Intelligence </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> you are under a particular and substantial obligation to comply with the letter and spirit of <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> Resolution 400. The Ethics <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> has determined that your statements gave the appearance that you were disclosing sensitive national security information and such appearance jeopardized the mutual confidence which must exist between the <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> and the intelligence community. Because the committee has concluded that your actions were not intentional, deliberate, nor attended with gross negligence, and because of the particular facts of this case, we will not recommend that the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> take institutional action against you. However, the committee wants to make it clear that it does not condone your actions.'' -LRB- Signed -RRB- Sen. <PERSON> Howell </PERSON> <PERSON> Heflin </PERSON>, chairman, Sen. <PERSON> Warren </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Rudman </PERSON>, vice chairman, and Sens. <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Pryor </PERSON>, <PERSON> Terry </PERSON> <PERSON> Sanford </PERSON>, <PERSON> Jesse </PERSON> <PERSON> Helms </PERSON> and <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Kassebaum </PERSON>.
