<HEAD>Machinists Leader Dug In Against Management</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DAN SEWELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. Chairman <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON>, irresistible cost-cutting force of the airline industry, has smacked into a seemingly immovable object at <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> _ veteran Machinists leader <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Bryan </PERSON> <PERSON> Bryan </PERSON>, a philosopher-mechanic who admits to being `` kind of a cornball sometimes,'' bases his strategies on his self-education in yoga, Zen, the Bible and history. `` It's kind of a Gandhi approach, or <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> <PERSON> Luther </PERSON> <PERSON> King </PERSON>. If you continue to be right, it's pretty hard for your adversary to overcome,'' <PERSON> Bryan </PERSON> said in a recent interview. But although <PERSON> Bryan </PERSON> quotes <PERSON> Khalil </PERSON> <PERSON> Gibran </PERSON> and gets misty-eyed over the selfless nobility of King <PERSON> Arthur </PERSON> and Sir <PERSON> Lancelot </PERSON> in `` Camelot,'' his favorite movie, passive resistance is not his only tactic. President of Machinists District 100 since 1979, <PERSON> Bryan </PERSON> represents 12,000, or more than one-third, of <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s employees. He has been blamed by former <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> chairman <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Borman </PERSON> for forcing the 1986 sale of the troubled carrier to Houston-based <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>. On April 13, <PERSON> Borman </PERSON>, vice chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION>, appeared with <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> Phil </PERSON> <PERSON> Bakes </PERSON> at a news conference aimed at countering a growing image that <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <O