<HEAD>Judge Orders Immigration Officials To Stop Harassing Salvadorans</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A federal judge has ordered the <ORGANIZATION> Immigration </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Naturalization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> not to use coercion to keep Salvadoran refugees from applying for political asylum. In a ruling released late Friday, <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> District Judge <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> V. </PERSON> <PERSON> Kenyon </PERSON> granted a petition for a permanent injunction ordering the <ORGANIZATION> INS </ORGANIZATION> to routinely inform all Salvadorans detained that they have a right to ask for political asylum, legal counsel and even access to pay telephones. The ruling reaffirmed a preliminary injunction <ORGANIZATION> Kenyon </ORGANIZATION> issued in 1982 in which he ruled that the <ORGANIZATION> INS </ORGANIZATION> routinely threatened Salvadorans to talk them out of their rights. <ORGANIZATION> INS </ORGANIZATION> attorneys had denied many of the allegations of abuses. Civil rights attorneys hailed the ruling. `` The decision really affirms the fact that Salvadorans with valid claims were simply being denied justice,'' said <PERSON> Linton </PERSON> <PERSON> Joaquin </PERSON>, executive director of the <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Refugee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION>, who helped argue the class-action lawsuit. The government's lead attorney in the case, <PERSON> Allen </PERSON> <PERSON> Hausman </PERSON>, criticized the decision, saying it offered sweeping protections to Salvadorans that are not enjoyed by other immigrants. `` How can you say a person from <LOCATION> Haiti </LOCATION> or <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> or <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> is less deserving? It's hard to distinguish,'' said <PERSON> Hausman </PERSON>, assistant director of the <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION